sec.p:
The ChemCam LIBS instrument was designed to obtain major element compositions for rocks and soils within seven meters of the instrument to a relative accuracy of ±10 %. The instrument must be capable of removing dust and weathering rinds, and must be able to profile to a depth of 1 mm into rocks. Table 2 lists the requirements specific to the ChemCam BU, mast-to-body fiber, and rover calibration targets to support these top-level requirements. Table 2
ChemCam body unit, optical fiber, and on-board calibration target functional requirements

